for @behindtheblinds by @aidancullen1 in @kenzo thank you loves !!

I’m at a loss for words. Ever since I was a little grom from growing up in sf skating around with the crew, hopping on muni to go halfway across the city to skate a spot, coming home waaaay late past curfew cuz we were skating a night spot or lighting something up, watching Phelps mob around Potrero and trying to land anything I could in front of the guy, bringing my homewrk to 6th and Fulton and not even doing it and just skating instead, through the broken bones, skitching on cars to make it up some of the fat hills only to bomb right back down them, spending daaaays at EMB and the island smoking weed and pushing around that smooth slippery ground soaking in the UV rays just smiling not a care in the world, hoppin Bart station to trek out to some of the spots across the bridge, I have always dreamt about getting a Thrasher cover. I don’t know if my pronunciation or typing is correct here or if my commas are in the right places. I’ve never been good with writing or putting my thoughts into sentences. Mostly just run on sentences. But I just want to say thank you. This is one of my biggest accomplishments. Work has been busy and I haven’t been able to skate as much as I used to and would like to but every time I do it is always fun and I still get that same feeling I would get as a kid. Tears of joy. This trick and spot has history to me too. Big thank you to uncle Tony @pivot_to_fakher . Big thank you to the fuckin lejjjjj @danz . Snapped the killlllller photo !! Thank you to the whole crew at @thrashermag !! HUGE thank you to my mom who help bandage me up and put neosporin all over my scars and back and my pops for not throwing out my board. And the big biggest thank you to all the SF and Bay Area natives that kept me pushing my entire life. Ups and downs !! Literally !! 
San Francisco, this one is for you !! 
🖤🧡
